---
/*
  Creation of Adam — scroll-driven moment.

  How it works:
  - Section is 160vh tall. Sticky child (100vh) keeps the scene
    visually centered while the user scrolls through ~60vh of
    "animation runway."
  - JS in site.js writes a 0→1 scroll-progress value into the
    section as --creation-p.
  - Hands use translateX bound to that progress: at p=0 they're
    at the edges, at p=1 they're touching at center.
  - The touch-light's opacity ramps from 0 → 1 across p=0.85 → 1.0,
    so the light only "ignites" right before the hands scroll out.
  - The light has a continuous pulse animation once visible.
  - Scrolling back up reverses the progress automatically.

  Required assets:
    /projects/hand-left.png   — Adam's hand (reaching from left)
    /projects/hand-right.png  — God's hand (reaching from right)
    Both PNGs should have transparent backgrounds. Aim for the
    fingertip near the edge of the canvas pointing INWARD.
*/
---

<section id="creation-of-adam" class="creation-section relative" aria-label="Where vision meets execution">
  <div class="creation-sticky">
    <img
      src="/projects/hand-left.png"
      alt=""
      class="hand hand-left"
      onerror="this.style.display='none'"
    />
    <img
      src="/projects/hand-right.png"
      alt=""
      class="hand hand-right"
      onerror="this.style.display='none'"
    />
    <div class="touch-light" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  </div>
</section>
